ing 3.5 million m3 of water daily, and about 5000 MW of electricity. The main technologies used to produce desalinated water in SWCC plants are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Multistage Flash (MSF).</li>\r\n	<li>Reverse Osmosis (RO).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFor more information, see SWCC online at <a href=\"http://www.swcc.gov.sa\">www.swcc.gov.sa</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LINKS AND MATERIAL</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>CLICK <a href=\"http://uk.prweb.com/releases/Hyperion/SWCC-RO-OTS/prweb11160561.htm\">HERE</a> TO VIEW THE RELEASE FROM PRWeb</li>\r\n	<li>CLICK <a href=\"http://www.hyperionsystems.net/images/stories/News/PressReleases/SWCC/201309-hyperionpressrelease-hyperiontosupplyrootstoswcctrainingcenterfinal.pdf\">HERE</a> TO DOWNLOAD THE RELEASE IN PDF (ENGLISH)</li>\r\n</ul>','Hyperion Simulation to supply the Reverse Osmosis OTS for the SWCC Training Center, in Saudi Arabia','','inherit','open','open','','411-revision-v1','','','2014-12-24 15:04:41','2014-12-24 13:04:41','',411,'http://localhost:8000/2014/12/24/411-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (418,2,'2014-12-24 15:04:55','2014-12-24 13:04:55','<strong>Nicosia, Cyprus</strong> Hyperion Systems Engineering (Hyperion), the leading independent solutions provider to the global process industries, announces that it will supply a generic Operator Training Simulator System (OTS) and the civil works of the OTS room for the Reverse Osmosis (RO) Project, at the Training Center of Saline Water Conversion Corporation (SWCC), in Saudi Arabia.\r\n\r\nHyperion Simulation will be the main supplier of the OTS system, and responsible for the functionality and handover of the complete system. Hyperion will also manage a sub-contractor, conducting the civil works portion of the project. To obtain more information on this and other Hyperion OTS projects, please visit: <a href=\"http://www.hyperionsystems.net/ots\">www.hyperionsystems.net/ots</a>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://www.hyperionsystems.net/images/stories/News/PressReleases/SWCC/genericotsarchitecture.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"409\" />\r\n\r\nHyperion Simulation’s responsibilities on the project will include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Development of the dynamic process models for the Reverse Osmosis (RO) plant, using DYNSIM™ dynamic simulation software.</li>\r\n	<li>Emulation of operator station (emulated DCS screens)</li>\r\n	<li>Emulation of the DCS controls</li>\r\n	<li>Emulation of the Safety System</li>\r\n	<li>Integration of the process models with the emulated Safety System and emulated DCS</li>\r\n	<li>Development of the Instructor Station</li>\r\n	<li>Hardware and software procurements</li>\r\n	<li>Installation and commissioning at SWCC Training Center</li>\r\n	<li>Provision of appropriate training and documentation (manuals and specifications)</li>\r\n	<li>Management of the subcontractor who will perform the civil works for the Reverse Osmosis OTS room of SWCC’s Training Center.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMr. Fahad Al-Minqash, Training Administration Manager of SWCC Trai